The course provides students with general principles of language learning and teaching and practical skills of lesson planning and administering as well as information and experience in assessment and marking.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1. To familiarize the Trainees with the latest trends in TEFL 2. To enable   the Trainees to plan, implement and evaluate teaching methods and techniques  3. To equip the Trainees with strategies and techniques for their trainee practice 4. To provide the Trainees with the means of enhancing their professional and personal development as TEFL teachersLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course, the students will be able to  1. Identify the importance of EFL in the curriculum, describe the learners of different age groups and list the roles of teacher in the language lesson and describe the characteristics of each role. 2. Discuss the characteristic features of a disciplined classroom, identify the areas of difficulty in classroom management and provide effective classroom management techniques. 3. Support the development of listening, reading, writing and speaking skills using different activities and strategies (incl. ICT resources) for that 4. Present vocabulary and grammar, teach pronunciation and find and modify activities for practising these areas     5. Use different correction techniques in oral and written work and develop their correction techniques in relation to the students. 6. Use different evaluation and marking techniques. Students will be able to produce classroom tests for testing all the language areas. 7. Plan their lessons during their trainee practice according to the requirements. 8. Analyse the lessons, use observation questionnaires and respond constructively to the feedback. 9. Promote learner independence and autonomy step by step in the classroom. 10. The students have compiled a portfolio and a dossier that reflects his/her progress in professional development
